te><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wacky-mysterious-paintings-by-this-surrealist-still-influence-contemporary-artists-an-exhibition-in-london-will-explore-the-legacy-of-rene-magritte-180989181/</guid></item><item><title>7000 年前，狩猎采集者将鳟鱼带到挪威山湖，这是人类转​​移鱼类的最早已知例子</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hunter-gatherers-brought-trout-to-a-norwegian-mountain-lake-7000-years-ago-the-earliest-known-example-of-humans-translocating-fish-180989167/</link><description>研究人员很早就知道这些动物被引入该地区的高海拔水域，但他们不确定这是什么时候发生的，也不确定人类是否有手。对最近发现的古代鱼陷阱的分析提供了新线索</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 15:42:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hunter-gatherers-brought-trout-to-a-norwegian-mountain-lake-7000-years-ago-the-earliest-known-example-of-humans-translocating-fish-180989167/</guid></item><item><title>你会与已故亲人的人工智能“幽灵”聊天吗？新研究表明该技术可以提供舒适感和封闭感</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/would-you-chat-with-an-ai-ghost-of-a-deceased-loved-one-new-research-suggests-that-the-tech-can-provide-comfort-and-closure-180989176/</link><description>商业“悲伤机器人”越来越受欢迎，许多专家对其心理和道德影响提出质疑。一项新研究旨在确保机器人的设计是负责任的</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/would-you-chat-with-an-ai-ghost-of-a-deceased-loved-one-new-research-suggests-that-the-tech-can-provide-comfort-and-closure-180989176/</guid></item><item><title>他们的名字已经消失在历史之中。但现在，您可以看到近 2000 年前他们生活在罗马时代城市时的面孔</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/their-names-were-lost-to-history-but-now-you-can-see-what-their-faces-may-have-looked-like-when-they-lived-in-a-roman-era-city-nearly-2000-years-ago-180989179/</link><description>布达佩斯的一个新展览展出了 16 个基于阿昆库姆古城出土头骨的面部重建作品。策展人不知道他们的生活细节，但他们发明了背景故事来填补空白</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/their-names-were-lost-to-history-but-now-you-can-see-what-their-faces-may-have-looked-like-when-they-lived-in-a-roman-era-city-nearly-2000-years-ago-180989179/</guid></item><item><title>视频捕捉到逆戟鲸猛烈撞击翻车鱼导致爆炸的画面。这种神秘的行为可能是一种游戏或青少年照顾的形式</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/video-captures-orcas-ramming-a-sunfish-so-hard-it-explodes-the-mysterious-behavior-might-be-a-form-of-play-or-juvenile-care-180989153/</link><description>在墨西哥加利福尼亚湾记录的两起事件中，逆戟鲸在杀死翻车鱼后共同将这些巨大的动物炸成碎片</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 04:00:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/video-captures-orcas-ramming-a-sunfish-so-hard-it-explodes-the-mysterious-behavior-might-be-a-form-of-play-or-juvenile-care-180989153/</guid></item><item><title>新研究发现，原住民精神领袖在这个澳大利亚洞穴中进行“魔法、治疗、诅咒”仪式已有 25,000 年之久</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/aboriginal-spiritual-leaders-performed-magic-healing-cursing-rituals-in-this-australian-cave-for-25000-years-new-research-finds-180989178/</link><description>考古学家与古奈库尔奈 (GunaiKurnai) 原住民社区的成员合作，在克洛格斯洞穴 (Cloggs Cave) 内探索了数千年前烧焦草中的灰烬层</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 21:25:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/aboriginal-spiritual-leaders-performed-magic-healing-cursing-rituals-in-this-australian-cave-for-25000-years-new-research-finds-180989178/</guid></item><item><title>孩子们可以在这座英国博物馆尝试“雾都孤儿”的生活方式，揭示维多利亚济贫院穷人的生活条件</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/kids-can-try-out-the-oliver-twist-lifestyle-at-this-english-museum-revealing-conditions-for-poor-people-in-a-victorian-workhouse-180989175/</link><description>经过修复后，里彭济贫院博物馆重新向公众开放，展示了英国 19 世纪“解决贫困问题”的景象、声音和规则</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 20:10:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/kids-can-try-out-the-oliver-twist-lifestyle-at-this-english-museum-revealing-conditions-for-poor-people-in-a-victorian-workhouse-180989175/</guid></item><item><title>SpaceX 火箭部件预计将于 8 月撞击月球，凸显日益严重的太空垃圾问题</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/A-spacex-rocket-part-is-expected-to-smack-into-the-moon-in-august-highlighting-the-growing-problem-of-space-junk-180989173/</link><description>这一意外事件还为科学家和天文观测者创造了实时目睹月球撞击动态的机会，尽管从地球角度来看，碎片会撞击月球阳光照射的部分，导致很难看到</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 19:44:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/A-spacex-rocket-part-is-expected-to-smack-into-the-moon-in-august-highlighting-the-growing-problem-of-space-junk-180989173/</guid></item><item><title>这封写于“泰坦尼克号”沉没前几天的信分享了船上二等舱乘客的观点</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-letter-penned-on-the-titanic-days-before-it-sank-shares-the-perspective-of-the-ships-second-class-passengers-180989174/</link><description>这封现正在拍卖的信描述了“泰坦尼克号”准备出发横渡大西洋时的好天气和熙熙攘攘的活动</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 17:59:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-letter-penned-on-the-titanic-days-before-it-sank-shares-the-perspective-of-the-ships-second-class-passengers-180989174/</guid></item><item><title>一项新的研究表明，人们并非生来就是右撇子或左撇子——他们通过练习来培养手的优势</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/people-arent-born-with-as-righties-or-lefties-they-develop-hand-dominance-with-practice-a-new-study-suggests-180989168/</link><description>人类确实有使用身体一侧的生物学偏好，这可能会促使他们使用该侧的肢体来完成书写等复杂的运动任务，并随着时间的推移磨练这些技能</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:59:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/people-arent-born-with-as-righties-or-lefties-they-develop-hand-dominance-with-practice-a-new-study-suggests-180989168/</guid></item><item><title>这场 20 世纪 50 年代的飞机灾难促使乘客进行了今天所熟知的飞行安全演示。搜索者刚刚在大西洋发现了残骸</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-1950s-airplane-disaster-prompted-the-flight-safety-demonstrations-passengers-know-today-seachers-just-found-the-wreckage-in-the-atlantic-ocean-180989170/</link><description>一组探险家使用自动水下航行器在距离波多黎各海岸约五英里的地方找到了泛美“奋进号”的残骸</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 15:02:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-1950s-airplane-disaster-prompted-the-flight-safety-demonstrations-passengers-know-today-seachers-just-found-the-wreckage-in-the-atlantic-ocean-180989170/</guid></item><item><title>双哈巴狗：观赏在圣地亚哥动物园野生动物园出生的可爱“双胞胎”针鼹</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/double-puggles-see-the-adorable-twin-echidnas-born-at-the-san-diego-zoo-safari-park-180989165/</link><description>据圣地亚哥动物园野生动物联盟称，这两只幼崽今年在同一个繁殖季节由一位母亲孵出，这种情况极为罕见</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/double-puggles-see-the-adorable-twin-echidnas-born-at-the-san-diego-zoo-safari-park-180989165/</guid></item><item><title>油管撑杆行走的新世界纪录为今年在阿拉斯加举行的世界爱斯基摩-印第安人奥运会带来了额外的兴奋</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-world-record-in-the-greased-pole-walk-brought-extra-excitement-to-this-years-world-eskimo-indian-olumpics-in-alaska-180989164/</link><description>这项年度体育赛事打破了 45 年来的纪录，该赛事通过指节跳和阿拉斯加高踢等活动来庆祝原住民的运动精神和文化</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 13:42:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-world-record-in-the-greased-pole-walk-brought-extra-excitement-to-this-years-world-eskimo-indian-olumpics-in-alaska-180989164/</guid></item><item><title>第二次世界大战期间，英国情报部门将这座豪宅变成了一个针对纳粹战俘的装有窃听器的间谍陷阱</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/british-intelligence-turned-this-mansion-into-a-bugged-spy-trap-for-nazi-prisoners-of-war-during-world-war-ii-180989166/</link><description>游客现在可以参观这座房子，德国将军们在楼上放松地闲聊，而为英国政府充当间谍和翻译的犹太难民则在地下室监听。</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 00:59:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/british-intelligence-turned-this-mansion-into-a-bugged-spy-trap-for-nazi-prisoners-of-war-during-world-war-ii-180989166/</guid></item><item><title>一名志愿者在英国国家档案馆偶然发现了一份奇怪的文件。原来是 1776 年 7 月印刷的《独立宣言》的稀有副本</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-volunteer-stumbled-upon-a-strange-document-in-the-uk-national-archives-it-turned-out-to-be-a-rare-copy-of-the-declaration-of-independence-printed-in-july-1776-180989169/</link><description>退休保险经纪人迈克尔·斯柯尔 (Michael Scurr) 在对伦敦档案馆存放的 18 世纪信件进行编目时发现了这段文字。这是美国以外唯一已知的同类副本</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 19:23:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-volunteer-stumbled-upon-a-strange-document-in-the-uk-national-archives-it-turned-out-to-be-a-rare-copy-of-the-declaration-of-independence-printed-in-july-1776-180989169/</guid></item><item><title>一项新的研究表明，裸鼹鼠皇后会散发出一种特殊的气味来阻止竞争对手繁殖</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/naked-mole-rat-queens-emit-a-special-scent-to-stop-their-rivals-from-reproducing-a-new-study-suggests-180989148/</link><description>这种长相奇怪的生物是已知的两种哺乳动物之一，它们的社会结构类似于蜜蜂和蚂蚁。一项新的研究表明，一种统治啮齿动物通过一种关键化合物来维持对群体的统治</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 19:14:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/naked-mole-rat-queens-emit-a-special-scent-to-stop-their-rivals-from-reproducing-a-new-study-suggests-180989148/</guid></item><item><title>附近的世界上可能存在生命吗？天文学家首次在宜居带的类地系外行星上发现了大气层</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-life-exist-on-this-nearby-world-in-a-first-astronomers-find-an-atmosphere-on-an-earth-like-exoplanet-in-the-habitable-zone-180989149/</link><description>虽然这个天体似乎拥有三个可以创造宜居环境的特征——大气层、岩石成分和可以让液态水停留在表面的温度——但研究人员目前尚未发现任何居民</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 16:23:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-life-exist-on-this-nearby-world-in-a-first-astronomers-find-an-atmosphere-on-an-earth-like-exoplanet-in-the-habitable-zone-180989149/</guid></item><item><title>一位业余天文学家使用谷歌地图发现了一个奇怪的凹痕。原来是3.9亿年前的陨石坑</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-amateur-astronomer-using-google-maps-spotted-a-strange-indentation-it-turned-out-to-be-a-meteorite-crater-from-390-million-years-ago-180989158/</link><description>科学家们通过对魁北克遗址的考察证实了天文学家的怀疑。这一发现提供了一个罕见的案例，即报道的新陨石坑被证明是真实的</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:58:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-amateur-astronomer-using-google-maps-spotted-a-strange-indentation-it-turned-out-to-be-a-meteorite-crater-from-390-million-years-ago-180989158/</guid></item></channel></rss>